      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay i get the clock thing. so it's more like they're just part of the same system rather than two separate things talking to each other. but if there's no actual signal or information being sent, how do physicists actually prove it's not just some hidden variable we haven't found yet? like, how do we know there isn't something \"under the hood\" making them match?",
      "source": "evaluator"
